'''Oyamazumi Shrine''' (大山祇神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in Nozawa, {{ill|Nishiaizu Town|ja|西会津町|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Yama District|ja|耶麻郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

==Enshrined Deities==
* {{ill|Ooyamatsumi|ja|オオヤマツミ|1=Ōyamatsumi|lt=Oyamatsumi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=大山祇命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|1=Iwanaga-hime|lt=Iwanagahime-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=岩長比売命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Konohananosakuyahime|ja|コノハナノサクヤビメ|lt=Konohananosakuyahime-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=木花咲耶姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

==History==
According to its tradition, this shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|778|ja|778th year|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|Hōki|ja|宝亀|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 9).

==Cultural Properties==
* Designated Natural Monument of Nishiaizu Town
** Cedar Avenue along the Uda Pilgrimage Route to Oyamazumi Shrine and the Shrine Trees within the precincts<ref>{{Cite web |type=Japanese publication |url=https://www.town.nishiaizu.fukushima.jp/soshiki/10/896.html |title=Cultural Properties of Nishiaizu Town (Town Designated) |website=Nishiaizu Town Official Website |publisher=Nishiaizu Town |language=ja |date= |accessdate=2024-08-22}}</ref>

