'''Oyamazumi Shrine''' (大山祇神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] located in Nozawa, [[:en:Nishiaizu, Fukushima|Nishiaizu Town]], [[:en:Yama District, Fukushima|Yama District]], [[:en:Fukushima Prefecture|Fukushima Prefecture]].

==Enshrined Deities==
* [[:en:Ōyamatsumi|Oyamatsumi-no-Mikoto]]
* [[:en:Iwanaga-hime|Iwanagahime-no-Mikoto]]
* [[:en:Konohanasakuya-hime|Konohananosakuyahime-no-Mikoto]]

==History==
According to its tradition, this shrine is said to have been founded in [[:en:778|778]] ([[:en:Hōki|Hōki]] 9).

==Cultural Properties==
* Designated Natural Monument of Nishiaizu Town
** Cedar Avenue along the Uda Pilgrimage Route to Oyamazumi Shrine and the Shrine Trees within the precincts<ref>{{Cite web |type=Japanese publication |url=https://www.town.nishiaizu.fukushima.jp/soshiki/10/896.html |title=Cultural Properties of Nishiaizu Town (Town Designated) |website=Nishiaizu Town Official Website |publisher=Nishiaizu Town |language=ja |date= |accessdate=2024-08-22}}</ref>

