'''Oyamazumi Shrine''' (大山祇神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|en|Shinto shrine|WD=Q845945|lt=Shinto Shrine|1=Shinto shrine}} located in Nozawa, {{ill|Nishiaizu, Fukushima|en|Nishiaizu, Fukushima|WD=Q784402|lt=Nishiaizu Town|1=Nishiaizu, Fukushima}}, {{ill|Yama District, Fukushima|en|Yama District, Fukushima|WD=Q1205228|lt=Yama District|1=Yama District, Fukushima}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|en|Fukushima Prefecture|WD=Q71707|lt=Fukushima Prefecture|1=Fukushima Prefecture}}.

==Enshrined Deities==
* {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|en|Ōyamatsumi|WD=Q386563|lt=Oyamatsumi-no-Mikoto|1=Ōyamatsumi}}
* {{ill|Iwanaga-hime|en|Iwanaga-hime|WD=Q8191705|lt=Iwanagahime-no-Mikoto|1=Iwanaga-hime}}
* {{ill|Konohanasakuya-hime|en|Konohanasakuya-hime|WD=Q1781862|lt=Konohananosakuyahime-no-Mikoto|1=Konohanasakuya-hime}}

==History==
According to its tradition, this shrine is said to have been founded in {{ill|778|en|778|WD=Q30452|lt=778|1=778}} ({{ill|Hōki|en|Hōki|WD=Q18520676|lt=Hōki|1=Hōki}} 9).

==Cultural Properties==
* Designated Natural Monument of Nishiaizu Town
** Cedar Avenue along the Uda Pilgrimage Route to Oyamazumi Shrine and the Shrine Trees within the precincts<ref>{{Cite web |type=Japanese publication |url=https://www.town.nishiaizu.fukushima.jp/soshiki/10/896.html |title=Cultural Properties of Nishiaizu Town (Town Designated) |website=Nishiaizu Town Official Website |publisher=Nishiaizu Town |language=ja |date= |accessdate=2024-08-22}}</ref>

